# Private Sales Context

> Copy this file to `context/sales-context.md`. The copied file is private and ignored by Git. Never put customer records, secrets or information your company does not allow into it.

Use [the About Me Worksheet](../templates/about-me-worksheet.md) to gather the basics. Use [the AI Sales Setup Prompt](../templates/ai-sales-setup-prompt.md) if you want to reuse the confirmed context as standing instructions in another AI tool.

## How to Mark Information

Use one of these labels for each section:

- `confirmed`: you or an approved source has verified it
- `inferred`: drafted from public information and waiting for your confirmation
- `unknown`: not supplied or not clear
- `to confirm`: a specific item you plan to check

Do not change an inference to confirmed until you have checked it.

## About Me

> Add your role, responsibilities and the sales work you actually do. Leave out passwords, personal identification and unnecessary employment records. Mark details you supply yourself as confirmed.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## What the Company Sells

> Add a short, plain English description of the product or service. Do not add confidential product plans, unapproved claims or private pricing. Public website wording remains inferred until you confirm it.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Who We Sell To

> Add the general customer types, industries, company sizes and buyer roles you work with. Do not add named customer or prospect records. Mark the description as confirmed, inferred or unknown.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Problems We Solve

> Add problems the company is genuinely equipped to solve. Do not present a public trend as proof that a specific prospect has the problem. Separate confirmed company positioning from assumptions about individual buyers.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Sales Process

> Add permitted sales stages, qualification checks and normal handover points. Do not infer internal stages from a public website or add a private process your company does not allow here.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Typical Stakeholders

> Add the roles commonly involved in a buying decision and what they usually need. Do not name real contacts or assume that a job title proves authority in a specific opportunity.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Products and Commercial Boundaries

> Add confirmed products, approved public price ranges and boundaries the AI must respect. Do not add private pricing, discount authority, contract terms or promises unless your company explicitly permits it.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Approved Sources

> List sources the agent may use, such as approved public pages, product guides or a permitted internal document. Do not list secrets, inaccessible private links or whole systems when one document is enough.

- Status: unknown
- Sources:

## Tools and Systems

> Add the general tools you use, such as a CRM, calendar or call recorder, and what each is the source of truth for. Do not add login details, API keys or private configuration.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Writing Style

> Add your preferred tone, formatting and phrases to avoid. Use sanitised examples of your own writing. Do not paste confidential customer messages.

- Status: unknown
- Notes:

## Actions Requiring Approval

> List actions the AI may prepare but must not complete without you, such as sending a message, changing the CRM, booking a meeting, quoting a price or sharing a file.

- Status: confirmed
- Always require my approval before:

## Information That Must Not Be Used

> List information that is prohibited, restricted or unnecessary for AI tasks. Do not copy the prohibited information into this section. Describe the category only.

- Status: confirmed
- Do not use:

## Unknowns and Items to Confirm

> Keep unresolved questions here rather than filling gaps with plausible answers. Add the owner or source needed for confirmation when known.

